A former National Publicity Secretary of the Ohanaeze Ndigbo, Chuks Ibegbu, has advised the National Leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Bola Tinubu and Atiku Abubakar of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, not to run for President during the 2023 general elections. Ibegbu said Tinubu and Atiku should drop their ambitions due to their age.  He added that Atiku, Tinubu and Vice President Yemi Osinbajo should rather pick a credible presidential candidate from the South-East noting that the rigorous nature of the Presidency wouldn’t allow the likes of Tinubu and Atiku to perform optimally at their age. Ibegbu’s comment came after Tinubu disclosed that he had informed President Muhammadu Buhari of his intention to run for the presidency in 2023. According to Daily Post, Ibegbu said, “I’m surprised that people like Tinubu have the audacity to come out, and I’m amazed that our Vice President, whom I see as a man of God, is also aspiring.



